long_desc.thetext:
Your package audacity failed to build from source in current rawhide.
https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=17704415
For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_26_Mass_Rebuild
This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 26 development cycle. Changing version to '26'.

Build issue was that the audacity manual.zip was changed to audacity-help.zip. The content dropped the top two folder layers with in the zip.
The spec was adjusted to extract the -help.zip into the earlier path. This allows the -manual package to be created and the package build succeeds.
Also build was adjusted to include mp3 import using libmad, which is now in the Fedora repository.
